Sixty-Six Wards Live 2018 Primary Election Tracker

Welcome to the Sixty-Six Wards turnout tracker! Voters across Philadelphia are sharing their turnout to support citizen science. First, vote! Then, share your Division and Voter Number at http://bit.ly/sixtysixturnout.

Live Results

As of 02:47, 500 voters in 66 wards have shared their data. I estimate that 140,709.4 people have voted across the city.

Maps

I use historical correlations among divisions’ turnout to estimate turnout in divisions in which nobody has shared data. I simultaneously estimate (1) the overall city-wide turnout, Divisions’ over-/under-performance, and the city-wide time pattern of voting.

Here are the current estimates of turnout in each division.
